  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "In the context of a form, \"designation\" typically refers to a person's job title or official position within an organization. It is a way of identifying the role or capacity in which the person is acting or to categorize their professional responsibilities. For example, if someone works as an engineer at a company, their designation would be \"Engineer.\" This information is often used to understand the individual's level of authority, responsibility, or expertise within the organization.",
